                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13579446" author="jbellis" created="Fri, 15 Feb 2013 19:35:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Another improvement (maybe for another ticket) would be to incorporate streaming MBps into severity as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13580459" author="vijay2win@yahoo.com" created="Mon, 18 Feb 2013 06:44:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached patch fixes the negative severity.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt; we should report based on how much IO we&apos;re using, since a 1T throttled to 5MB/s is less impactful than a 100MB running at full speed&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Well I am not sure about that, 100MB without throttle may be on SSD&apos;s and 1TB may be on Spindles.... So looking at the throttle might not help and we should assume the user did the right thing on throttle.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Another possible option: Create a way to get IOStat data into the JVM and measure the IOWait time but the problem is how do we support MS Windows? not sure if there is a generic way to do so.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I would suggest we do both Streaming and IOWait monitor in another ticket, Makes sense?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13580652" author="jbellis" created="Mon, 18 Feb 2013 15:18:57 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Another possible option: Create a way to get IOStat data into the JVM and measure the IOWait time but the problem is how do we support MS Windows? not sure if there is a generic way to do so.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I like that idea a lot better than trying to special-case streaming and compaction.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;No idea how to get that info on Windows though.  Guess we could fall back to MBPs compaction/streaming there.  (Yes, this is not perfect if you mix SSDs + HDDs, but it&apos;s a LOT better than total MB of compaction.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13590605" author="jbellis" created="Fri, 1 Mar 2013 15:05:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on the fix for negative severity.  Please open followup tickets per above discussion.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13591238" author="vijay2win@yahoo.com" created="Sat, 2 Mar 2013 02:45:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to 1.2 and trunk, opened &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-5306&quot; title=&quot;Improve Dsnitch Severity&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-5306&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-5306&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; as a followup. Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
